Nippon Columbia Co Ltd &lt;NCOL.T> will makea one-for-20 bonus stock issue on July 14 to pay back remainingpremiums accumulated by 4.5 mln shares issued at market pricethrough public placement in September 1980, a spokesman said.    The bonus issue will bring its outstanding capital sharesto 65.02 mln from 61.92 mln as at March 31 1987. It is open toshareholders registered on May 31.    Nippon Columbia's share price fell 20 to 1,260 yen on theTokyo Stock Exchange today. REUTER&#3;